        "Precipitation state",
        "Fatigue property",
        "Micromechanism"
      ],
      "research_type": "experimental",
      "paper_scope": "Systematically investigate the tension-tension fatigue behavior and deformation mechanisms of solution-treated and aging-treated Fe-30.5Mn-8Al-1C austenitic low-density steels, clarify the critical role of κ-carbide precipitation state in controlling fatigue properties, and provide guidance for the development of fatigue-resistant low-density steels for automotive applications"
